19. Docilis has much more authority than any other form, is recognized by the scholiast, and is found elsewhere as the name of a sreedman. Dolichos ‘Long ’ would be suitable enough as the name of a gladiator, if it had more authority. The old commentators were divided in opinion, according to Porphyrion, as to whether Castor and Docilis were actors or gladiators; but as they seem to be matched, the latter is the more probable.
